{"name":"Giahuaghn Nuamor","size":"medium","type":"fiend","tag":"shapechanger","alignment":"chaotic lawful","hitDice":"5","armorName":"scale mail","shieldBonus":2,"natArmorBonus":8,"otherArmorDesc":"14","speed":"30","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":true,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"34 (4d8+18)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"13","dexPoints":"12","conPoints":"14","intPoints":"12","wisPoints":"16","chaPoints":"9","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"60","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"0","telepathy":0,"cr":"5","customCr":"3 (700 XP)","customProf":2,"isLegendary":false,"legendariesDescription":"The doppelganger can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The doppelganger regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the doppelganger can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the doppelganger can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The doppelganger can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":false,"mythicDescription":"If the doppelganger's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using {Some Ability}.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the doppelganger's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the doppelganger dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Shapechanger","desc":"[MON] can use its action to polymorph into a Small or Medium humanoid it has seen, or back into its true form. Its statistics, other than its size, are the same in each form. Any equipment it is wearing or carrying isn't transformed. It reverts to its true form if it dies."},{"name":"Flesh recollection","desc":"As part of _Shapechanging_ into a target [MON] can access some of their memories. While polymorphed into a humanoid it has met, [MON] can gain any one skill proficiency, tool proficiency, or language from the target.\n\nAdditionally, [MON] can make a constitution check to recall some of the memories from the target. The DC is 10 + target's level/CR, but may be modified.\n- With a token or item from the target (such as a piece of clothing or a wax seal) a the DC is lowered by 2.\n- With a personal affect (such as a diary, letter, jewelry) the DC is lowered by 4.\n- With some of the target themselves (i.e. a lock of hair or drop of blood) the DC is lowered by 8.\n\nOn a failure [MON] takes psychic damage equal to a number of d12s equal to 1 + the targets level/CR, but on a success it may ask 3 questions about the target's past. This feature may only be used once per target."},{"name":"Sunlight Sensitivity","desc":"While in sunlight, [MON] has disadvantage on attack rolls, as well as on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight."},{"name":"One with Shadows","desc":"When [MON] is in an area of dim light or darkness, it can use your action to become invisible until it moves or takes an action or a reaction."},{"name":"Ambusher","desc":"[MON] has advantage on attack rolls against any creature it has surprised."},{"name":"Surprise Attack","desc":"If [MON] surprises a creature and hits it with an attack during the first round of combat, the target takes an extra [3d6] damage from the attack."},{"name":"Shelter the Unfaithful","desc":"Certain religious acolytes may get a certain feeling about you and render discrete aid, others may get the same feeling and react with violence."}],"actions":[{"name":"Warhammer","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [STR 1D8] bludgeoning damage (versatile 1d10)."},{"name":"Light Crossbow","desc":"_Ranged Weapon Attack:_ [DEX ATK] to hit, range 80/320 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [DEX 1D8] piercing damage."},{"name":"Cantrips","desc":"[MON] knows and can cast _Thaumaturgy_, _Guidance_, and _Spare the Dying_"},{"name":"Beseech the Outer God","desc":"[MON] may call upon power from an enigmatic and malevolent source to trigger one of the following effects:\n\n_Turn the Masses_: Any humanoid within 30ft must make a DC [WIS SAVE] wisdom saving throw or be turned for 1 minute or until they take damage. (search \"turn undead 5e wikidot\" for rules)\n\n_Siphon Vitals_: Melee Weapon Attack: [WIS ATK] to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: [3D8] necrotic damage. [MON] heals for half of the damage dealt.\n\n_Bolster Pawns_: [MON] and up to 5 creatures it can see within 30ft gain [WIS 1d8] temporary hit points.\n\n_Channel Arcana_: Cast a warlock spell at 3rd level (as determined by an Outer God, but you may negotiate. Search \"warlock spell list 5e wikidot\" for ideas)\n\nHowever, using this power, especially multiple times per day, is damaging to the soul and exhausting to the body.\n- After the first usage [MON] cannot take reactions until its next turn.\n- After the second usage [MON] is stunned until the start of its next turn.\n- After the 3rd and each subsequent use [MON] takes [1d8] necrotic damage _and_ is stunned until the start of its next turn.\nThis counter resets each night at sunset."}],"bonusActions":[],"reactions":[],"legendaries":[],"mythics":[],"lairs":[],"regionals":[],"sthrows":[{"name":"con","order":2},{"name":"cha","order":5}],"skills":[{"name":"deception","stat":"cha","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"medicine","stat":"wis"},{"name":"perception","stat":"wis"},{"name":"survival","stat":"wis"}],"damagetypes":[],"specialdamage":[],"conditions":[{"name":"charmed"}],"languages":[{"name":"Abyssal","speaks":true},{"name":"Common","speaks":true},{"name":"Undercommon","speaks":true}],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"Giahuaghn","pluralName":"","doubleColumns":true,"separationPoint":3,"damage":[]}